## Frida Rules
- API: `Process.getModuleByName('libc.so').getExportByName('send')` (NOT `Module.findExportByName`)
- Game networking: hook BOTH `send()` + `recv()` + `recvfrom()` (games alternate)
- Console output: ASCII only, no Unicode symbols (causes cp1252 errors on Windows)
- Memory values: try Double (64-bit) first for Flash/AIR games, then Float, then Int32

## Code Style
- No unnecessary comments/docstrings
- Test directly on emulator, no mocks
- Python scripts: unbuffered output (`python -u`)
- Frida JS: use `var` not `let/const` (compatibility)
